description: Viking Supply Ships AB engages in the provision of logistics solutions and marine transports. The company is headquartered in Stenungsund, Vastra Gotalands and currently employs 740 full-time employees.  The Company’s operations are structured into two business areas: TransAtlantic and Viking Supply Ships. The TransAtlantic business area provides logistics solutions in the area of vessel transport, with its Roll-on/Roll-off (RoRo) and container vessels, as well as ship management with technical operation and manning to external clients. The Viking Supply Ships business area comprises several offshore vessels, which operate in the offshore and icebreaking market, primarily in the North Sea, Arctic and subarctic areas. The Company’s main shareholder is Kistefos Holding AS.
naics: Deep Sea, Coastal, and Great Lakes Water Transportation
